title: FP Review
name: SANTA CLARA UNIVERSITY </br>
description: AMMR - To follow CBC base code for H occupancy rooms. Per CBC and CFC Chapter 50, Section 5004.2.1 and 5004.2.2 - Secondary containment is only required if individual vessels having capacity of more than 55 gallons or aggregate capacity of multiple vessels exceeds 1000 gallons. This building will be under these quantities and therefore secondary containment and spill control would not be required. Forthing coming change in the next code cycle to the City of Santa Clara ordinance to elimate all quantities of chemicals required to be secondarily contained.  Therefore we are using the base code for the H3/H4 chemical storage room.

name: SANTA CLARA UNIVERSITY </br>
description: AMMR - Code requires a manaul ventilation system emergency shutoff switch outside the chemical room.  There is a SFM exception that does not require the shut-off when the exhaust is exhausted 100% to the outside.   The room exhaust is currently designed to be 100% exhausted to the outside. If the buidling was designed to be a Group L-occupancy the exception could be used.  Since the chemical storage room is very small we believe the exception should be allowed for this Goup B-occupancy.

title: FP Review
name: CITY OF SANTA CLARA REDEVELOPMENT  </br>
description:
PCC - Fire fees paid - PCC Date = 7/2/19 - Project Planner = Nimisha Agrawal. 
Rezoning of a 2.47 acre City-owned vacant site from Single Family residential (R1-6L) to Planned Development (PD) to support the construction of a single building ranging in height from two to three stories and containing 65 residential affordable units in a mix of studios and one-, two- and three bedroom units. The project intends to provide housing for a broad range of family sizes and incomes, including 20% set aside for people with developmental disabilities.
